## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/   # Reusable UI components
├── pages/        # Route-level components
├── api/          # Backend API routes
├── lib/          # Shared utilities
└── types/        # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Coding Standards
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Components: functional with hooks, no class components
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- All async functions must handle errors explicitly
- No `console.log` in production code — use the logger utility

## Architecture Decisions
- API routes follow REST conventions: GET/POST/PUT/DELETE
- State management: React Query for server state, Zustand for UI state
- Authentication: JWT tokens, stored in httpOnly cookies
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod validation

## Common Commands
```bash
npm run dev         # Start development server
npm run build       # Production build
npm run test        # Run test suite
npm run lint        # Check for lint errors
npm run db:migrate  # Run pending migrations
```

## Environment Variables
See `.env.example` for required variables. Never commit `.env` directly.

## Review Checklist
- [ ] Tests pass (`npm run test`)
- [ ] No lint errors (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] .env.example updated if new variables added
- [ ] API changes documented in docs/api.md

## Notes for Claude Code
- Always run `npm run lint` after editing TypeScript files
- Database migrations go in `src/db/migrations/` with timestamp prefix
- When adding new API routes, update the OpenAPI spec at `docs/openapi.yaml`
